04/02/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the BiH Joint Military Commission reached an agreement Tuesday (3 February) on the draft structure of the country's future armed forces. The commission agreed that the future army would be composed of three brigades -- two from the Federation of BiH (FBiH) and one from Republika Srpska (RS) -- as well as air forces, logistics and training units. The military would consist of 12,000 professional soldiers: 8,000 from FBiH and 4,000 from RS. (OHR Sources, PBS BiH, BH Radio 1, BBC, Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne novine - 04/02/02; Federation TV, BBC - 03/02/04)
